<div id="review_412489716" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/412489716" />
    <a title="Neil" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/482722-neil"><img alt="Neil" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1191699972p2/482722.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/412489716?book_show_action=true">Sep 11, 2012</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Neil" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Neil" href="/user/show/482722-neil">Neil</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was ok"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was ok</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9780385489515" href="/book/show/16235.Sister_of_My_Heart">review of another edition</a>


          <div>
    <span class="greyText">Recommended to Neil by: </span>
      Book Club
  </div>


          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/482722-neil?shelf=hb-book-club">hb-book-club</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer412489716" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer4641292271766303214"><b>Polished Prose, Soap-Opera Story</b> - The author evokes some vivid imagery, and the book moves along smoothly enough. But the plot is straight out of the sappiest soap opera or Bollywood film, and the feminist message is crudely formulated. Every man in the book is a liar, a fool, or a coward - and most are all three. The two main women make every serious life decision as if they were 13 year old girls in the throes of their own hormone-driven emotions. My sympathy for their often horrible situatio</span>
  <span id="freeText4641292271766303214" style="display:none"><b>Polished Prose, Soap-Opera Story</b> - The author evokes some vivid imagery, and the book moves along smoothly enough. But the plot is straight out of the sappiest soap opera or Bollywood film, and the feminist message is crudely formulated. Every man in the book is a liar, a fool, or a coward - and most are all three. The two main women make every serious life decision as if they were 13 year old girls in the throes of their own hormone-driven emotions. My sympathy for their often horrible situations wears somewhat thin by the end of the book.<br /><br />Having said that, the author can turn a phrase, and she shines when writing the fairy tales that the main characters tell each other.</span>
  <a data-text-id="4641292271766303214" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


