<div id="review_2951680802" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2951680802" />
    <a title="Neha" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/58679848-neha"><img alt="Neha" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1493241703p2/58679848.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2951680802?book_show_action=true">Aug 28, 2019</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Neha" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Neha" href="/user/show/58679848-neha">Neha</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9780385489515" href="/book/show/16235.Sister_of_My_Heart">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2951680802" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer4631802133313500200">I was conflicted between a 3.5 and a 4 for this book.<br/><br/>This story has been woven against a backdrop of old Calcutta, of two cousins whose love is truly unconditional and who share an immensely strong bond that goes beyond blood relations. The lives of Sudha and Anjali have a lots of twists and turns, fate putting them in situations that are believable and yet spice the story with an appropriate amount of drama. The storyline was strong and compelling, making it hard to put the book down past half-</span>
  <span id="freeText4631802133313500200" style="display:none">I was conflicted between a 3.5 and a 4 for this book.<br /><br />This story has been woven against a backdrop of old Calcutta, of two cousins whose love is truly unconditional and who share an immensely strong bond that goes beyond blood relations. The lives of Sudha and Anjali have a lots of twists and turns, fate putting them in situations that are believable and yet spice the story with an appropriate amount of drama. The storyline was strong and compelling, making it hard to put the book down past half-point, and the narration was good for most parts. The headstrong-ness and rebelliousness of Anju has been contrasted well against the more meek and submitting Sudha. The three mothers they share a household with - Gauri Ma, Nalini Ma and Pishi Ma have really different personalities, which I think the author brought out really well as the story progressed. <br /><br />I was disappointed though in the way the author built the backdrop of the story - it took me a good 100 pages (and even now I am not sure) to place the book in time. My initial thoughts, having been unable to place the era were that the author was over-stereotyping the customs, the casteism etc. Later however, piecing together the clothing and movies especially as the story progressed, I decided to give the author the benefit of doubt and tried mentally placing the story a decade or two further back. At the point, the story became a really enjoyable read!<br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="4631802133313500200" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


