    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_1502849068" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1502849068" />
    <a title="Nadira" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/51241595-nadira"><img alt="Nadira" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1452254734p2/51241595.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1502849068?book_show_action=true">Jan 09, 2016</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Nadira" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Nadira" href="/user/show/51241595-nadira">Nadira</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9780385489515" href="/book/show/16235.Sister_of_My_Heart">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/51241595-nadira?shelf=owned-books">owned-books</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1502849068" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer5774797098879149456">“I guess there&apos;s a lot we hope for that never happens. Or perhaps it is just that desire lies at the heart of human existence. When we turn away from one desire, we must find another to cleave to with all our strength - or else we die.” <br/><br/>Sister of My Heart by Chitra Banerjee Divakaruni is one of my top ten favorite books. The story centers on the lives of two Indian girls, Anju and Sudha, who are technically cousins. They grow up in a household run by their three mothers: Pishi, Gouri, and Nalini</span>
  <span id="freeText5774797098879149456" style="display:none">“I guess there's a lot we hope for that never happens. Or perhaps it is just that desire lies at the heart of human existence. When we turn away from one desire, we must find another to cleave to with all our strength - or else we die.” <br /><br />Sister of My Heart by Chitra Banerjee Divakaruni is one of my top ten favorite books. The story centers on the lives of two Indian girls, Anju and Sudha, who are technically cousins. They grow up in a household run by their three mothers: Pishi, Gouri, and Nalini. They are inseparable as best friends and sisters but their personalities are in stark contrast to each other. Beautiful and calm, Sudha is a storyteller and dreams of designing clothes and having a family. Anju has a fierce spirit and longs to study Literature in college. The girls use their own voices to narrate the story of their lives. In alternating chapters the reader closely follows the lives of the two sisters through childhood, adolescence, and early adulthood. Although some of the characters immigrate to the United States, most of the story is set in India. Sister of My Heart is a story about family, friendship, and the bond between sisters.<br /><br />This was one unbelievably good read! I simply loved it!! Beautiful descriptions, beautiful story and the best part was that it had a sequel - The Vine of Desire! The family relationships may seem complicated, but they play an important role in the novel. The characterization and plot twists about Love, Separation, Reunions and dark family secrets take you on a very captivating, enchanting journey. You almost feel like you might be watching a movie! The story is based in Calcutta, but being a Bengali I was able to quite relate to the traditions and cultures portrayed. The novel does use a lot of South Asian and Bengali clichés and words. Hope that doesn’t turn off or derail the readers from this beautiful story. The author’s language is so poetic and her elaborate descriptions will transport you to the streets of Calcutta with so much ease. Very easy read and I highly recommend this book for its compelling story.</span>
  <a data-text-id="5774797098879149456" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


